<BR>
Oh there was an instance where a magician wore a wonderous robe<BR>
that "looked" like the fabled Robe of Alendine, but it turned <BR>
out to be a Robe of the Elements.<BR>
<BR>
I do not claim to know everything, since I have yet to visit the <BR>
kingdom of the almighty God of Fear. However, I did state, that <BR>
if it DID exist, there would be proof of it.<BR>
<BR>
I know the robe of the kedge exists for I have seen it, touched it,<BR>
examined it with mine own eyes. I know shiny metallic robes exist,<BR>
for it seems to be the popular style nowadays, as well as the ever<BR>
elusive robe of ishva. But you know, I begin to wonder if the god<BR>
of fear exists, since I have never seen him either.<BR>
<BR>
(OOC) Some of you take these posts as gospel. Thanks for <BR>
defending my rp words, I had no idea it would be taken as<BR>
a "know it all comment". Next time, I'll just be a lurker <BR>
and not post any information at all, then where would this<BR>
database of information be?<BR>
<BR>
Kierxhai, currently discovering the Ruins of Kunark<BR>
